## Component Naming
- Component file names must use kebab-case

Example: 
create-modal.tsx
user-profile-card.tsx

- Component name must use PascalCase

Example: 
CreateModal
UserProfileCard


- Component name must match the file name

Example: 
create-modal.tsx -> CreateModal
user-profile-card.tsx -> UserProfileCard

- Prefer default export for page-level or feature-level components
Example: 
const CreateModal = () => {}
export default CreateModal

- Prefer named export for shared reusable UI components


## Large Component Structure
- Keep components small and focused

- If  a component becomes too large or handles multiple responsibilities, convert it into a folder structure

Example:

Before:
create-modal.tsx

After: 
create-modal/
    index.tsx
    modal-header.tsx
    modal-form.tsx
    modal-footer.tsx
    types.ts

- Use `index.tsx` as the main entry component

- Child components should stay in the same folder

- Shared logic should be extracted into hooks or utility files

- Avoid files longer than 200-300 lines unless clearly justified

- Prefer extracting child components before adding more conditional rerendering

- If a component contains more than 3 major UI sections, consider folder structure refactoring